snippet.textDisplay: Some of these comments are atrocious! What is wrong with people? There's nothing wrong with him beyond what he discussed here in this interview! Props to the interviewer for being so patient and awesome at his job! I love that he treated justin as another human being just chilling and talking life instead of some groupie asking shallow vapid questions. He's incredibly authentic, intelligent, and probably the best interviewer I've seen in a really long time. I'm a 33 year old mother of 4. I don't know much about justin other than what I've heard my kids talk about, or what I've seen on social media. My heart has always hurt for him in the same way my heart hurt for Britney spears. I'm inspired by him.  Im so grateful for his honesty. I think especially in today's world, it's incredibly important to have people with influence that are honest about the human condition.  Mental health is so important, and it needs to be talked about! We all experience things in life that hurt. Things we're coping with. Sometimes we need help expressing those feelings in a way that's conducive to our healing.  The boys in my generation were not allowed to show any emotion. If they did they were ridiculed and called a pussy. I hope to see more of this genuine honesty in 2020 from everyone. I never thought I'd be able to relate to justin bieber, but the truth is, we have so much in common. I know what it feels like to live with adhd, addiction, anxiety, and depression. I've lived with them for the majority of my life. My teenage years and early 20s were some of the hardest times of my life.  I couldn't imagine living that out in the public eye.  It's really sad, and disgusting how we treat certain celebrities as if they're not human beings with feelings, and a family, and a life outside of being an entertainer. I've never understood idolizing someone like that.  I appreciate artist and their work. Im thankful for those artist that are honest and vulnerable. Perhaps if all were this humble, and honest, and vulnerable then none of them would be dehumanized by the public.  They would just be another greatly talented person sharing their stories to inspire others, and hopefully motivate people to be their best selves. His future looks bright, and that wife of his is absolutley gorgeous! I hope his years to come are filled with love and happiness. I hope people will respect his right to live his life in peace and privacy! Don't do the same thing to him that was done to Britney spears. He's given the public his entire childhood.  He deserves to have some time to his self. It sucks that he doesn't read comments like this bc if all the trash comments.

snippet.textDisplay: Mental health doesn’t give a shit who you are. The only difference between Justin and I or any one else is our story. We all feel the feelings just for different reasons (sometimes for the same). Justin you should be proud of yourself. Your speaking on behalf of so many of us. Unconditional love is the definition of god (my opinion). I truly believe I’m forgiven and loved for me. We are all human. In one way or another we’re all the same. We come into this world with nothing and we leave the world the same way. What we do in between that time is what matters. Money doesn’t buy happiness nor does it prevent depression or anxiety or love. My journey is different then Justin’s or anyone else’s. There’s so much truth in hearing someone else’s journey that you don’t even realize your not alone. Mental health is just as important and severe as cancer. The stigma needs to go. Thank you Justin for telling your story. I relate all too well and your music.......I get goosebumps. I hope one day I’m strong enough to tell my own story. God bless y’all 💜
